I deleted an external link, because it was not a credible resource. The link, referenced a poem that was purpotedly, written by "Black Shawl". (Black Shawl was one of the two wives, of the Lakota War Chief, Crazy Horse). The poem was not however, written by Black Shawl. It was written by a contemporary writer, Irene Latham. Latham wrote the poem, based upon her own musings, as to what she believed, that Black Shawl, would have expressed, had she, written the poem.
